== Awards ==<!-- This section is linked from [[Lexus]] -->
{{further|[[List of awards won by the Lexus LS]]}}

Notable examples of awards received by the Lexus LS include [[World Car of the Year]] (WCOTY),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wcoty.com/media/?release=32&year=2007|title=Lexus LS 460 - 2007 World Car of the Year|accessdate=2007-04-08|publisher=[[World Car of the Year]]|date=2007-04-05}}</ref> [[International Car of the Year]] (ICOTY),<ref name=ICOTY>{{cite web|url=http://www.roadandtravel.com/awards/2007/awardsbg/awardsbg_luxury.htm|last=Hindes|first=Martha|title=2007 ICOTY Most Respected Luxury Car of the Year|accessdate=2007-04-08|publisher=Road & Travel|date=2007-01-06}}</ref> [[Japan Car of the Year]] (JCOTY),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jcoty.org/press/press.html#1111|title=2006-2007 Car of the Year Japan|accessdate=2007-04-08|publisher=Car of the Year Japan|date=2006-11-18|language=Japanese}}</ref> [[Canadian Car of the Year]],<ref name=Canada>{{cite web|url=http://www.ajac.ca/web/ccoty/previous_byyear.asp|title=AJAC winners by year|year=2007|accessdate=2007-05-15}}</ref> [[Wheels Car of the Year|''Wheels'' Car of the Year]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wheelsmag.com.au/wheels/site/articleIDs/C40CA2CB6C8577F1CA257285001E7302?open&template=domWheels|title=Wheels' COTY the real McCoy|last=Gable|first=Chris|2006-12-04|accessdate=2007-05-15}}</ref> and [[Top Gear (current format)|''Top Gear'']] Limousine of the Year.<ref>"Top Gear Car of the Year". ''Top Gear''. 2006-12-13.<!-- http://www.topgear.com/content/news/stories/1429/.-->Retrieved on 2007-05-15.</ref> The Lexus LS has been the highest-rated luxury car in ''Automobile Magazine,''<ref name=autocomp>{{cite web| url=http://www.automobilemag.com/features/awards/2002lexusls430/|title=2002 Best Luxury Car Over $40,000 - Lexus LS 430|year=2002|accessdate=2007-05-31|work=Automobile Magazine}}</ref> ''[[Car and Driver]]'',<ref name=showdown>Bedard, Patrick. Comparison Test: Showdown ''Car and Driver'', Vol. 35, Issue [[6 December]], [[1989]]</ref><ref name="caranddriver.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.caranddriver.com/comparisons/7359/70000-luxury-sedans-page7.html|title=$70,000 Luxury Sedans|date=2003-12|accessdate=2007-04-08|work=Car and Driver|last=Bedard|first=Patrick|date=2003-12}}</ref> ''Consumer Reports'',<ref name=bestcar>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessweek.com/innovate/content/sep2005/id20050915_721163.htm|title=Lexus LS 430: More Luxury for Less|accessdate=2007-04-08|last=Peterson|first=Thane|work=BusinessWeek|date=2005-[[September 16|9-16]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-33790663_ITM|<!-- http://news.yahoo.com/s/usnw/20071001/pl_usnw/infiniti_m35_retains_top_spot_in_consumer_reports__tests_of_six_luxury_sedans -->|title=Consumer Reports Ultra-Lux Face-off, October 2007|accessdate=2007-10-01|last=Consumer Union|work=Consumer Reports}}</ref> ''Fleet World'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.easier.com/view/News/Motoring/Lexus/article-116704.html|title=Lexus LS wins Best Luxury Car in Fleet World Honours|date=2007-05-18|accessdate=2009-05-22|publisher=Easier Motoring UK}}</ref> and ''[[MotorWeek]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mpt.org/motorweek/dc2007/05.shtml|title=Motorweek 2007 Driver's Choice Awards|year=2007|work=MotorWeek|accessdate=2007-05-15}}</ref> In J.D. Power's long-term Vehicle Dependability Study, the Lexus LS has been the most reliable car for fifteen consecutive years,<ref name=reliability>{{cite web|url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-8916172_ITM|title=Test Drive: Lexus LS 430|work=[[Orlando Sentinel]]|accessdate=2009-02-22|date=2004-07-29|last=Smith |first=Steven}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jdpower.com/corporate/news/releases/pressrelease.aspx?ID=2006133|title=J.D. Power and Associates 2006 Vehicle Dependability Study|accessdate=2009-04-01|publisher=J.D. Power|date=2006-08-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jdpower.com/corporate/news/releases/pressrelease.aspx?ID=2007130|title=J.D. Power and Associates 2007 Vehicle Dependability Study|date=2007-08-09|accessdate=2007-08-09|publisher=[[J.D. Power and Associates]]}}</ref> the most for any manufacturer,<ref name=vdsawards>{{cite web|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/pressRelease/idUS168266+07-Aug-2008+PRN20080807|title=Toyota Motor Sales Earns 11 Awards in 2008 J.D. Power and Associates Vehicle Dependability|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=2009-04-14|date=2008-08-07}}</ref><ref name=2009vds>{{cite web|url=http://www.jdpower.com/corporate/news/releases/pressrelease.aspx?ID=2009043|title=J.D. Power and Associates 2009 Vehicle Dependability Study|date=2009-03-19|accessdate=2009-04-01|publisher=[[J.D. Power and Associates]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jdpower.com/corporate/news/releases/pressrelease.aspx?ID=2008115|title=J.D. Power and Associates 2008 Vehicle Dependability Study|date=2008-08-07|accessdate=2009-04-01|publisher=[[J.D. Power and Associates]]}}</ref> and ''Consumer Reports'' has ranked the sedan as the most reliable vehicle tested.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forbes.com/2006/02/17/reliable-luxury-cars-cx_dl_0221feat_ls.html|title=Most-Reliable Luxury Cars 2006|work=Forbes|accessdate=2009-04-13|last=Leinert|first=Dan|date=2006-02-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.consumerreports.org/cro/cars/new-cars/buying-advice/who-makes-the-best-cars/overview/|title=Car brands reviewed|work=Consumer Reports|accessdate=2009-04-13|last=Consumer Union|date=2009-04}}</ref><ref name=CRreliability>{{cite web|url=http://www.theautochannel.com/news/2007/02/28/038601.html|title=Consumer Reports: 2007 New Car Reliability Predictions, Mercedes-Benz Last|work=[[Consumer Reports]]|accessdate=2009-02-22|date=2007|last=Consumer Union}}</ref><ref name=reliablecar>
{{cite web|url=http://www.cars.com/go/crp/buyingGuides/Story.jsp?section=Luxury&story=luxReliable2006&subject=stories&referer=&year=New|title=Finding and Keeping a Reliable Luxury Car|accessdate=2007-04-08|last=Palmer|first=Beth|publisher=Cars.com|date=2006-02-11}}</ref> Safety awards include ''[[Auto Bild]]'''s 2007 Innovation Prize for the LS 460 pre-collision system,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.co.uk/cgi/news/release?id=192479 |title="Auto 1" Awards, Auto Bild Group|accessdate=2007-04-08|work=Auto Bild|date=2007-03-07}}</ref> consecutive first place rankings in the ''[[What Car?]]'' Security Supertest,<ref>"What Car? Security Supertest 2005". ''[[What Car?]]''. 2004-12.<!-- http://www.whatcar.co.uk/news-article.aspx?NA=212739. -->Retrieved on 2007-04-29.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.testdriven.co.uk/lexus-wins-what-car-security-supertest-for-fifth-year/|title=Lexus wins What Car? Security Supertest for fifth year |publisher=TestDriven|accessdate=2009-05-21|date=2004-12}}
</ref> and ''[[Kiplinger's Personal Finance|Kiplinger's]]'' "Best in Safety for Cars $40,000 and Over".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kiplinger.com/personalfinance/features/archives/2004/11/40over.html|title=2005 Car Buyer's Guide|accessdate=2007-04-08|work=Kiplinger's Personal Finance|date=2004-11}}</ref> Technical honors range from [[Ward's 10 Best Engines]],<ref>"Ward's Ten Best Engines 1999" (1999-01) ''[[Ward's AutoWorld]]''.</ref><ref>"Ward's Ten Best Engines 2000" (2000-01) ''Ward's AutoWorld'',</ref> to [[Edmunds.com]]'s "Best Sound System in Cars Over $30,000",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.edmunds.com/reviews/list/top10/58886/article.html|title=Edmunds Top 10 Sound Systems in Cars Over $30,000|accessdate=2009-05-22|publisher=Edmunds.com|last=Memmer|first=Scott|date=2002}}</ref> and the [[Society of Automotive Engineers]] (SAE) 2007 "Best Engineered Vehicle" award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sae.org/servlets/productDetail?PROD_TYP=PAPER&PROD_CD=1-115-4-88|title=:Lexus LS 460: AEI's Best Engineered Vehicle for 2007|publisher=Society of Automotive Engineers|date=2007-04|accessdate=2007-04-09}}</ref>

